MetaData.Company Description: Elite DhobiLite is a laundry and dry cleaning service provider that offers convenient and high-quality laundry solutions to customers.Dhobilite provide services such as wash and fold, dry cleaning, and ironing. Their platform allows customers to schedule pickups and deliveries. Apart from that we provide free pickup and delivery services.
MetaData.Our Business Model: Elite DhobiLite operates on a B2C (Business-to-Consumer) model, providing laundry and dry cleaning services directly to individual customers. Customers can easily schedule pickups and deliveries through the platform
MetaData.Our franchising model: Elite DhobiLite's franchising model allows entrepreneurs to partner with the brand and operate their own laundry and dry cleaning businesses under the Elite DhobiLite name. The model typically includes training, marketing assistance, and access to a comprehensive operational framework. Franchisees can leverage the company's expertise.

typesOfFranchises.title: Master
typesOfFranchises.description: A Master Franchise serves as the central processing hub for multiple Retail franchises. It is equipped with laundry and dry cleaning machinery. Retail franchises depend on the Master Franchise for all processing tasks, including washing, dry cleaning, and ironing. The Master Franchise charges processing fees to the Retail franchises.

typesOfFranchises.title: Live
typesOfFranchises.description: This type of unit provides showroom-like visibility and is fully equipped with all necessary laundry machinery to handle the complete service cycle.  This model is well-suited for  tier-3 cities areas with moderate demand, enabling comprehensive, end-to-end service from a single location. If a Live Unit is equipped with sufficient machinery to support 3-4 Retail franchises, it is referred to as a hybrid setup.

typesOfFranchises.title: Retail
typesOfFranchises.description: A Retail Franchise acts as a customer-facing collection and delivery point. It does not have in-house laundry or dry cleaning machinery, but is equipped with a reception area and storage racks for handling orders. Runners are responsible for collecting orders from customers and delivering them to customer. The Retail Franchise manages all customer interactions, including handling complaints and queries, ensuring a smooth customer experience.

MetaData.Runner: A Runner is responsible for collecting articles from customers and delivering them. Runners are our brand face which directly interacts with customers, they are responsible to be in a presentable form and also responsible to collecting the payment from the customer at the time of delivery.
MetaData.Msentinel: Msentinel is a mobile application used internally by the employees and the franchises, it manages the entire workflow of order such as pickup and delivery management, placing orders of inventory, center information like analytics, slot management etc.
MetaData.Sentinel: Sentinel is a web application used internally by the employees and the franchises, it manages the entire workflow of order such as pickup and delivery management, placing orders of inventory, center information like analytics, employee onboarding , franchisee ledger etc.

Our Order flow / Workflow.Ongoing leads/Team View: when customer place the orders from customer application then the order first arrives in ongoing leads section of Msentinel. In ownwer id it will reflect as ongoing leads and in manager id it will reflect as team view. Now the next step is that the owner or manager will assign the order to the respective runner for pickup.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Assigned order: When an order is assigned to a runner by the owner or manager, it appears in the 'Assigned Order' section of the Msentinel app in the runner Id. The runner can view all assigned orders along with customer details such as name, address, and contact number. The runner then accepts the order, confirms the customer's availability at the pickup location, and proceeds to collect the articles or clothes from the customer.
Our Order flow / Workflow.E-challan: When a runner arrives at the customer's location. It enters details of the acrticles such as type of article and quantity in Msentinel. E-challan will not proceed if the runner does not click the photo of the articles.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Invoice generation: After the order is picked up, the manager at the center is responsible for generating the final invoice. Before generating the invoice, the manager must cross-verify the picked items with the e-challan created by the runner at pickup. If there is any discrepancy,it must be resolved. Without invoice generation our center will not proceed with the order processing.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Tagging of the cloths: After the invoice is generated, each item is tagged with a unique customer tag ID to ensure accurate tracking and processing. This tagging process is essential to prevent article mix-ups during cleaning and delivery. The tags include information such as the customer tag ID , date of pickup, service and the count of clothes.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Workshop Hub or w_hub: This step not applicable for live units. Here the orders are moved from retail unit to master unit , once the orders are received by the master unit the order should be marked as 'workshop hub', the manager verifies the tagged items against the invoice generated at pickup. Acceptance by the Workshop(w_hub) confirms that the articles are now under their responsibility for further processing.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Processing of the cloths: The articles are  washed, cleaned as per the service at the processing unit.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Packing of the cloths: After processing the articles, are packed and marked in Msentinel.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Hub: This is not applicable for live units.After packing, the packed order are moved to retail unit and retail has to confirm the same by accepting on Msentinel. And the order is ready for delivery.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Order delivery: Manager/owner assigns the order to the runner for delivery. The runner will accept the order and deliver the articles to the customer.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Ratings given by the customer: After delivery, customers can rate their experience. There are two types of ratings: 'quality rating' (reflects order cleaning and servicing , this is the responsibility of processing unit) and 'PD rating' (this indicated how well pickup and delivery service provided to the customer and this is responsibility of the unit which is doing pickup and delivery).

Terms used in workflow.title: E-Challan
Terms used in workflow.description: An electronic document generated by the runner at the time of pickup, containing details of the items collected and their estimated processing costs. It serves as a preliminary invoice and helps in tracking the order.

Terms used in workflow.title: Invoice
Terms used in workflow.description: A formal bill generated by the manager after verifying the items against the E-Challan. It includes final pricing for the processing of the particular order.

Terms used in workflow.title: Tagging
Terms used in workflow.description: The process of attaching unique identifiers to each item for tracking purposes throughout the processing and delivery stages.

Terms used in workflow.title: Processing
Terms used in workflow.description: The cleaning, dry cleaning, ironing, and packing of items as per customer specifications.

Terms used in workflow.title: logistics
Terms used in workflow.description: Transfer of arcticles from one center to another, such as from a Retail franchise to a Workshop or from a Workshop to a Retail franchise for final delivery to the customer.

Revenue share between franchises and com.title: Master Franchise and Retail Franchise
Revenue share between franchises and com.description: In most of the cases this is the sharing between the parties involved. The Master Franchise retains 43% of the total revenue generated from the orders processed at its center, while the Retail Franchise also retains 43%. The franchise responsible for handling logistics receives a 7% share of the total revenue. The remaining 7% is allocated to the company as royalty.

Revenue share between franchises and com.title: Live Unit
Revenue share between franchises and com.description: In most of the cases this is the sharing between the parties involved. If it doesnt have any dependent Retail franchises, the Live Unit retains 93% of the total revenue generated from the orders processed at its center. The remaining 7% is allocated to the company as royalty. But if it has dependent Retail franchises then the revenue share will be same as Master Franchise and Retail Franchise.

Terms and condition.5: Company accepts no liability for items whose loose color, specially when color of one part of the garment gets on the other part.
Terms and condition.6: Company is not responsible for any article which is left beyond 30 days. After this period, if any discount was given on this order at the time of pickup shall be removed and a storage fees shall be charged @12% per month on the total invoice amount. Article not claimed within three months shall be handled appropriately by Company and be sold to recover the billed charges.
Terms and condition.7: Company reserves the right to refuse cleaning any garment.
Terms and condition.8: Removal of stain is a part of the process but, complete removal of stains can not be guaranteed and will be processed at customer's risk.

Terms and condition.10: If customer cannot accept the loss of any garment, please do not leave it with us.
Terms and condition.11: In case of any loss or damage Company can reimburse up to a maximum of three (3) times of its processing (laundry / dryclean) cost (decision remains with Company if any reimbursement has to be done) only if Customer is able to produce the bills. Compensation shall be provided in form of services and no cash will be given to customer.
Terms and condition.12: Customers are requested to count the articles at the time of delivery and inform the delivery man in case of missing articles. Company will not be responsible for any such claims after the articles delivery has been accepted and signed by the customer.
Terms and condition.13: Company gives a warranty of 7 days from the date of delivery for the articles, for any quality related issues with washing or dry-cleaning of articles (only if the article has not been used by the customer after service). Any quality related claim after the stipulated time shall not be entertained.

Terms and condition.15: Company shall not be held responsible for any ornaments/ jewellery fittings on the garment.
Terms and condition.16: Customer shall examine articles for damage at the time of delivery, and notify the same at that time. Company shall not be responsible for any claims afterwards.

Terms and condition.19: Some process/items may require additional period to process. No deduction on billed amount or claim can be initiated against in respect of delays.
Terms and condition.20: Tariff for designer wear will be decided on a case to case to case basis depending on the complexity of garment, the same shall be communicated to customer after it is examined by the expert at the processing center.

Terms and condition.1: Company does not provide printed bills, and invoices will be sent by e-mail only on registered email id.
Terms and condition.2: Customer will be charged twice the amount of regular order for any express delivery.
Terms and condition.3: Customer has to pay the entire amount after successful delivery of order.
Terms and condition.4: For retail orders, customer has to pay by cash only. We accept debit or credit cards as well, but for that customer has to inform us beforehand.
Terms and condition.5: Customer can buy a prepaid plan for which amount can be paid by cash or cheque. In case customer chooses to pay by cheque, the plan will only be effective after realization of the cheque.
Terms and condition.6: Tax will be charged over and above the rates mentioned on the website.
Terms and condition.7: Prepaid plans are valid at all DhobiLite retail locations across India, irrespective of the location where the plan was originally purchased.
Terms and condition.8: Any cashback provided to the customer will be given as services and no money will be refunded. This cashback amount will be added to the customer's DhobiLite account.

Terms and condition.Cancellation / Refund Policy: Cancellation / Refund Policy are given below
Terms and condition.1: Any extra amount paid by the customer for a retail order can be refunded by the company if the customer requests it.
Terms and condition.2: Balance available in 'Prepaid' plans is non-refundable and cannot be transferred to any other customer.
Terms and condition.3: User can cancel at any time before the actual pick-up. No cancellation charges will be levied.
Terms and condition.4: If the company denies processing any article for any reason, the order amount for that article will be refunded to the retail customer or added to the prepaid balance for prepaid plan customers.
Terms and condition.5: If the customer wants to cancel the order for any reason, the cancellation request must be placed within 2 hours of pickup of the articles.
Terms and condition.6: Once the order is punched and processed, it cannot be cancelled.

Terms and condition.1: Coupons can only be applied by the customer using the DhobiLite mobile app on available platforms.
Terms and condition.2: Once an order is placed and the invoice is generated, coupons cannot be applied.
Terms and condition.3: No two or more discounts, coupons, or offers can be clubbed together.

Columns.Title: centerBilling
Columns.description: Total amount billed at the particular center including retails billing(if applicable) for the current month up to today.

Columns.Title: lyMtdCenterBilling
Columns.description: Total amount billed at the particular center including retails billing(if applicable) for the same month last year till today's date last year.For example, if today is March 15, this represents the total amount billed at the center in March 15 of the previous year.

Columns.Title: lastMonthCenterServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total service amount billed to customers at the center including retails service billing(if applicable) in the last month.

Columns.Title: lyCenterBilling
Columns.description: Total service amount billed at the center, including retail service billing (if applicable), for the same month last year. For example, if the current month is March, this represents the total service billing for March of the previous year.

Columns.Title: centerAvgBilling
Columns.description: Total service amount billed at the center including retail service billing (if applicable) in last 365 days divided by 12.

Columns.Title: lyCenterAvgBilling
Columns.description: Average monthly service amount billed at the center, including retail service billing (if applicable), for the previous year. Calculated as the total service billing for the last 730 days minus the total for the last 365 days, divided by 12.

Columns.Title: thisMonthCenterClothCount
Columns.description: Total number of articles received at the center in the current month till today, including retail articles (if applicable).

Columns.Title: lyMtdCenterClothCount
Columns.description: Total number of articles received at the center till today in the same month last year, including retail articles (if applicable). For example, if today is March 15, this represents the total number of articles received at the center in March 15 of the previous year.

Columns.Title: lmCenterClothCount
Columns.description: The total number of articles received at center last month including retail articles (if applicable).

Columns.Title: lySameMonthCenterClothCount
Columns.description: Total number of articles received at the center including retail articles(if applicable) in the same month last year. For example, if the current month is March, this represents the total number of articles received in March of the previous year.

Columns.Title: lastMonthMasterShare
Columns.description: The processing charge of the last month ,received by the master from the  retail centers they are serving.

Columns.Title: lySameMonthMasterShare
Columns.description: The processing charge of the last year, received by the master from the retail centers they are serving in the same month last year. For example, if the current month is March, this represents the processing charge received in March of the previous year.

Columns.Title: masterAvgShare
Columns.description: Total processing charge received by the master center from their corresponding retail centers in the last 365 days divided by 12.

Columns.Title: lyMasterAvgShare
Columns.description: Total processing charge received by the master center from their corresponding retail centers in the last 730 days (365+365) minus the total processing charge received in the last 365 days, divided by 12.

Columns.Title: yearCenterClothCount
Columns.description: Total number of articles received at the center in last 365 days.

Columns.Title: lyCenterClothCount
Columns.description: Total number of articles received at center in last 730 days (365+365) - total number of articles received at center in last 365 days.

Columns.Title: top3GarmentServiceBilling
Columns.description: Out of all the articles processed by the master of all retails they are serving, this indicates the service billing for the top 3 articles. For example, if coat billing is 50k rupees, shirt billing is 30k rupees, and shoes billing is 20k rupees, these would be the top 3 considering all other articles have lower billing amounts.

Columns.title: last3MonthCenterAvgBilling
Columns.description: This is the average of the total service billing of all the retails that the master is serving over the past 3 months. For example, if the total service billing for the last 3 months is 5 lakh of the 4 retails that the master is serving, then the average will be 5 lakh divided by 3.

A higher percentile (e.g., 90) means the center receives more complaints than 90% of centers. Lower values are better, indicating fewer complaints relative to peers.

Columns.title: l2lmRunnerRatingInDetail
Columns.description: This means the average rating of each individual runner at a center in the last to last month. Customer can give this rating by evaluating the runner's performance, such as pickup, delivery, communication, behavior etc.

Columns.Title: companyLedgerAmount
Columns.description: Monthly settlement amount between the franchise and the company. If positive, the franchise owes this amount to the company; if negative, the company owes this amount to the franchise.

Columns.Title: runningcompanyLedgerAmount
Columns.description: The real-time running balance between the franchise and the company. If positive, the franchise owes this amount to the company; if negative, the company owes this amount to the franchise. This value is updated continuously as transactions occur.

Columns.Title: pendingAmountInCenter
Columns.description: The total amount pending from customers whose orders have been delivered but payment has not yet been received. This amount is outstanding at the center and should be collected from the respective customers.

Columns.Title: withMeRunners
Columns.description: After a runner delivers an order, the total amount of that order is automatically transferred to the runner's 'with me' account. withMeRunners is the total amount in the 'with me' account of all the runners at the center.

Columns.Title: serviceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount of the services rendered to the customers in the current month.

Columns.Title: lyMtdServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total billing of the services rendered  to customers in the same month till date last year. For example, if today is March 15, this represents the total service billing from March 1 to March 15 of the previous year.

Columns.Title: compensation
Columns.description: Compensation is the amount that is paid to the customer for inconvenience caused like damage, missing article, etc. It is the total amount paid to the customer in the current month at the center.

Columns.Title: lastMonthServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total billing of the services rendered to the customers in the last month.

Columns.Title: lyServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total billing of the services rendered to the customers in the same month last year. For example, if the current month is March, this represents the total service billing for March of the previous year.

Columns.Title: yearlyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: Total service billing in the last 365 days generated at the center divided by 12.

Columns.Title: lyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: Total service billing in the last 730 days (365+365) minus the total service billing in the last 365 days, divided by 12.

Columns.Title: avgTicketSize
Columns.description: Total service billing at the center divided by total number of orders in the current month.

Columns.Title: lmAvgTicketSize
Columns.description: Total service billing at the center divided by total number of orders in the last month.

Columns.Title: yearAvgTicketSize
Columns.description: Average ticket size at the center for the last 365 days, calculated as total service billing divided by the total number of orders in the last 365 days.

Columns.Title: lastYearAvgTicketSize
Columns.description: Average ticket size at the center for the previous year. It is calculated as: (total service billing in the last 730 days minus the total service billing in the last 365 days) divided by the total number of orders in the last 730 days minus the total number of orders in the last 365 days.

Columns.Title: thisMonthClothCount
Columns.description: Total number of articles received at the center in the current month.

Columns.Title: lyMtdClothCount
Columns.description: Total number of articles received at the center in the same month till date last year. For example, if today is March 15, this represents the total number of articles received at the center from March 1 to March 15 of the previous year.

Columns.Title: lmClothCount
Columns.description: Total number of articles received at the center in the last month.

Columns.Title: lyClothCount
Columns.description: Total number of articles received at the center in the same month last year. For example, if the current month is March, this represents the total number of articles received in March of the previous year.

Columns.title: top3GarmentServiceBilling
Columns.description: Out of all the articles received by the particular center, this indicates the service billing for the top 3 articles. For example, if coat billing is 50k rupees, shirt billing is 30k rupees, and shoes billing is 20k rupees, these would be the top 3 considering all other articles have lower billing amounts.

Columns.title: acceptedAmount
Columns.description: Total amount of all orders that are delivered and the sharing of the amount is done. Sentinal automatically accept the invoice after one or two days of delivery and does the sharing of the amount in gst(tax), company(royalty), processing charge and partner share (center share).

Columns.title: partnerShare
Columns.description: The share of the center from the accepted amount, which is calculated as the accepted amount minus company(royalty) and processing charge if the center is not doing its own processing.

Columns.title: cashCollection
Columns.description: Cash collected in this month by the runners at the center, this does not include any online payments made by customer to the company directly.

Columns.title: washServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount of the only washing services rendered to the customers in the current month. This means it does not include any dry clean or value add service billing.

Columns.title: dryCleanServiceBilling
Columns.description: Service billing of dry clean service at the center. It only consist of only garments that are dry cleaned, not the garments that are washed or value added services.

Columns.title: valueAddServiceBilling
Columns.description: Service billing of value added services such as shoe cleaning , bag cleaning etc. at the center. It does not include any wash or dry clean service billing.

Columns.title: lastMonthWashServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount of the only washing services rendered to the customers in the last month. This means it does not include any dry clean or value add service billing.

Columns.title: lastMonthDryCleanServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount of the dry clean services rendered to the customers in the last month. It only consist of only garments that are dry cleaned, not the garments that are washed or value added services.

Columns.title: lastMonthValueAddServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount of the value added services such as shoe cleaning , bag cleaning etc. rendered to the customers in the last month. It does not include any wash or dry clean service billing.

Columns.title: lyWashServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount of the only washing services rendered to the customers in the same month last year.This means it does not include any dry clean or value add service billing. For example, if the current month is March, this represents the total service billing for wash service in March of the previous year.

Columns.title: lyDryCleanServiceBilling
Columns.description: Last year same month service billing of dry clean service at the center. It only consist of only garments that are dry cleaned, not the garments that are washed or value added services. for example, if the current month is March, this represents the total service billing for dry clean service in March of the previous year.

Columns.title: lyValueAddServiceBilling
Columns.description: Last year same month service billing of value add service at the center. It does not include any wash or dry clean service billing. For example, if the current month is March, this represents the total service billing for value add service in March of the previous year.

Columns.title: washYearlyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: It is calculated as total wash service billing in the last 365 days divided by 12.

Columns.title: dryCleanYearlyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: It is calculated as total dry clean service billing in the last 365 days divided by 12.

Columns.title: valueAddYearlyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: It is calculated as total 'value added services' service billing in the last 365 days divided by 12.

Columns.title: lyWashLyYearlyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: It is calculated as total wash service billing in between 365 and 730 days, divided by 12.

Columns.title: lyDryCleanLyYearlyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: It is calculated as total dry clean service billing in between 365 and 730 days, divided by 12.

Columns.title: lyValueAddLyYearlyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: It is calculated as total 'value added services' service billing in between 365 and 730 days, divided by 12.
